Vector of 90 Distruct colours

Source: R/pophelper.R
distructColours.Rd

Vector of 90 Distruct colours.

distructColours()

Value

Returns a character vector of 90 colours recognised by Distruct.

Examples

distructColours();

#>  [1] "orange"       "blue"         "yellow"       "pink"         "green"       
#>  [6] "purple"       "red"          "light_green"  "dark_blue"    "light_purple"
#> [11] "light_yellow" "brown"        "light_blue"   "olive_green"  "peach"       
#> [16] "sea_green"    "yellow_green" "blue_purple"  "blue_green"   "gray"        
#> [21] "dark_green"   "light_gray"   "red2"         "light_blue2"  "light_orange"
#> [26] "dark_gray"    "light_pink"   "dark_brown"   "dark_orange"  "dark_purple" 
#> [31] "white"        "color32"      "color33"      "color34"      "color35"     
#> [36] "color36"      "color37"      "color38"      "color39"      "color40"     
#> [41] "color41"      "color42"      "color43"      "color44"      "color45"     
#> [46] "color46"      "color47"      "color48"      "color49"      "color50"     
#> [51] "color51"      "color52"      "color53"      "color54"      "color55"

#> [61] "color101"     "color102"     "color103"     "color104"     "color105"    
#> [66] "color106"     "color107"     "color108"     "color109"     "color110"    
#> [71] "color111"     "color112"     "color113"     "color114"     "color115"

#> [81] "color121"     "color122"     "color123"     "color124"     "color125"

#> [1] "orange" "blue"   "yellow" "pink"   "green" 
distructColours()[10:15];

#> [1] "light_purple" "light_yellow" "brown"        "light_blue"   "olive_green"
